HEADWORD: activation
<hw>activation</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the process of making
active.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> energizing, activating</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <sn>2.</sn> <def>making active and
effective (as a bomb).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>certain devices, as bombs or artillery shells, are designed to
be unable to operate until a specific action (activation or arming) is
taken to make them operable.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>activator</ent>⟦br⟧
